	 <title>iMatches</title> 
	 <para></para> 
	 <bridgehead renderas="sect3">Remarks</bridgehead> 
	 <para><symbol>matches</symbol> is the parser recognized symbol for this
		  operator. This operator matches using regular expressions. This operator
		  functions similar to <symbol>like</symbol>. For Information on how this is
		  handled, see the .NET documentation for Regular Expression Classes (linked
		  below).</para> 
	 <example> 
		  <title>Example</title> 
		  <programlisting>select Employee where Name matches "^Jo";</programlisting> 
		  <programlisting>ID Name 
-- ---- 
1  Joe 
2  John 
3  Josh</programlisting> 
	 </example> 
